O-O 9. d5
{ The only move which can trouble Black. White blocks the long diagonal, so we strive to open it with }
9... e6 10. Bg5 Na6
{ It's surprising that this normal developing move is a novelty. It prepares Nc7 or Nc5 in some cases. }
11. Rc1 exd5 12. cxd5
{ The critical continuation, and one of White's best continuations in the whole 3. e3 system. }
12... Nc7 { More and more pressure is put on the d5-pawn. } 13. Qd2 Rc8
{ With a nice idea in mind. } 14. Bc4 b5
{ A nice trick! Black already stands at least equal, and I analyze some moves further in this line to prove that fact. }
