{ A jarring check, based on some tactical points. } 8. Nc3
{ This is the only move played so far. } 8... Ne4
{ 8...Nd4  is played in the only encounter, but it should have been strongly refuted with  9.Bg5!  Nc2+  10.Kd1  Nxa1  11.Bxf6  followed by Nd5, winning the game. }
9. Qd3 f5
{ The star knight on e4 should be maintained, even at the cost of slightly weakening the kingside. }
10. e3 { Intending Be2, but also blocking the c1-h6 diagonal. } 10... d6 11.
Be2 Be6 12. O-O Nxc3 { Wrecking White's structure. } 13. bxc3 Rd8
{ Both of White's bishops are blocked behind his own pawns and Black's pieces are very well placed. Black has an excellent game. }
