7. Be3
{ The best, yet unplayed move. Having seen Black's tactical tricks, it is logical to cover the b6-square. }
7... d5 { Securing the dominant position of the e4-knight. } 8. c3 e6 9. Nd2
{ Offering the exchange of knights which will somewhat extricate White's position. }
9... Nd6
{ Playing for more than equality, which is everything we have after  9...Nxd2  . }
10. g3 Be7 11. Bg2 Nf5 { The dark-square bishop is again the target. } 12. Bf4
g5 { Give White no respite to organize his pieces. } 13. Be5 f6 14. Bd4 e5
{ The bishop is almost trapped. Here White is lucky to have a defensive resource that doesn't lose instantly. }
