15... dxe4 { The pawn must be taken, even at the cost of king safety. } 16.
Qh5+ { Both king moves are possible, but I prefer } 16... Kf8
{ 16...Kd7!?  is a typical bizarre suggestion of the engine, but in the end, the text looks more natural to me. }
17. Be3 { A sad but forced move. } 17... Nxe3 18. fxe3 Kg7
{ Castling 'by hand' is the best way to bring pieces out. } 19. Bxe4 Qe8
{ If we manage to exchange queens the endgame would be very pleasant for us, as we have the bishop pair and a ready-to-roll kingside majority. }
20. Qf3 { Declining the offer. } 20... h5
{ Gaining space on the kingside. White's position is already very tough here, but he'd be better advised to refrain from }
21. Bxb7 Bg4 22. Qg2 Rb8
{ Black is clearly winning as White's king won't be able to find a safe shelter and White has too many weaknesses in his camp. }
