{ A lethal discovered check is coming, so White must run his king further up the board. }
16. Kg3 Ne7
{ Clearing the 6th rank for the queen. We are completely winning, so I want to show you what will happen if the courageous king goes further. A word of warning: it's not so easy to find and remember this backward retreat. In fact, at the moment I'm writing this sentence  (1 month after publication)  , 59% of the students have gotten this move wrong when reviewing! }
17. Kxg4 Re4+ 18. Kg3 Nf5+ 19. Kh3 Qh6+ 20. Nh4 Qxh4#
{ An elegant mate! Not every day you win in 20 moves, right? } *

