{ This leads to very sharp positions, where a mistake from both sides can be fatal. However, our attacking moves are natural and easy to make, while there are several pitfalls for White on the way. We already see that in the 11. Bxe5 variation. Various ideas from that variation are applicable here, for example, the Nxe3 sacrifice. }
12. Bxe5 Re8 { White faces a choice between bishop retreats. } 13. Bg3
{ There is a small difference to @@StartFEN@@r1bq1rk1/pp3ppp/2n5/3np3/8/P1B2N2/1P2PPPP/R2QKB1R w KQ - 0 11@@EndFEN@@  11.Bxe5  Re8  12.Bg3  ,  which is the knights f3 and c6. The knight on f3 is a target to Bg4 ideas in that line, but it also covers the unimportant-looking h4-pawn. We can exploit that tiny change with }
13... h5
{ Harry@@StartBracket@@ or Huy?@@EndBracket@@ the h-pawn confidently steps forward. The bishop on g3 unexpectedly becomes a target as h5-h4 is in the air. }
14. Qd4 { The best move, centralizing the queen while holding up h5-h4. } 14...
Bg4
{ The engine slightly prefers  14...Bf5  ,  but I think this move is both more natural and gives White more chance to go wrong. }
15. Rd1 { Attacking the d5-knight. } 15... Qe7
{ A cold-blooded sacrifice that must be planned in advance. White seems to be dead lost, but luckily for him, he has a brilliant defensive concept that helps him to reach an inferior ending. }
16. Qxd5 { 16.e3?  is met by, as usual,  16...Nxe3!!  17.fxe3  Rad8  -+ } 16...
Bxe2 { We seem to be winning, but White has a resource. } 17. Bh4
{ Deflecting the queen. Note that  17.Bd6  is a different move order that transposes. Now our best try is to enter a forced sequence with }
17... Bc4+ 18. Bxe7 Rxe7+ 19. Be2
{ 19.Kd2  Bxd5  gives us the advantage due to our far more active pieces. }
19... Rxe2+ 20. Kf1 Rd2+
{ 20...Rc2+  21.Qxc4  Rxc4  is another slightly better endgame for us, but I think White can hold the draw easier than after the text. }
21. Qxc4 { White is forced to enter a 2 rooks vs queen endgame. } 21... Rxd1+
22. Ke2 Rxh1
{ After a series of punches by both sides, we are at the endgame. Even though we have a slight material advantage, White's queen is quite active. The endgame should be drawn with the best play, but we are already playing for two results. }
*

