{ Now we can develop 'normally' and reach a middlegame which the addition of the h-pawn moves favour us as f5-f4 will come with greater effect. Sometimes the crazy g7-g5 is playable too. }
9... Be6 10. Bg2 Be7 11. O-O Ng4 { White no longer has h3 to kick our knight. }
12. Nd5 { This seemingly natural move is met with a shocking blow. } 12... Bxh4
{ Unleash the dynamic beast behind Black's set-up! } 13. gxh4
{ This loses, but otherwise we are a clear pawn up with a continuing attack. }
13... Qxh4 14. Re1 Qxf2+ 15. Kh1 Qg3 16. Kg1 h4
{ h3 is coming, with a winning advantage. } 17. Nc7+ Kd7 18. Nxa8 h3
{ It's the end of the story. } *

