cxb7 Bxb7 11. e4
{ I believe this is White's best move, as he gains space in the centre and attacks the b5 pawn. }
11... Qd7 { 11...Bxe4?  12.Bxb5+  Ke7  isn't the nicest Bongcloud. } 12. Qb3
Bc6 { The b5-pawn is rock-solid. } 13. Bd3 Be7
{ Our chief idea is the d5 break, but for the time being king safety is more important. }
14. O-O O-O 15. Be3 d5
{ Finally, Black is ready for the action and opens up the centre! } 16. exd5
Bxd5 17. Qxb5 Qxb5 18. Bxb5 Rxa2
{ With a balanced ending in which Black is no worse. We should keep in mind possibilities to attack the isolated b2-pawn and roll our kingside majority. }
