7... a6 { Now White has two options. } 8. Bxf6
{ Destroying our pawn structure at the cost of the bishop pair. } 8... gxf6
{ Of course  8...Qxf6  loses to  9.Nd5 } 9. Na3 f5
{ We actively use our doubled pawns as an asset and gain space in the centre. }
10. e3 Be6 11. Qd2 f4
{ A nice idea, temporarily sacrifice a pawn to open the game. } 12. Nc2
{ Refusing to take the offer. } 12... Bh6 13. O-O-O Qa5
{ Swinging the queen over and setting a trap. } 14. Qxd6
{ This greedy move deserves a punishment. } 14... Rd8
{ White's queen only has one square. } 15. Qa3 Qxa3 16. Rxd8+ Kxd8 17. bxa3
fxe3 18. Nxe3 Na5 { And White's structure is in ruins. } *

