6. Nc3 { The best move, developing the knight and attack the b5-pawn. } 6... a6
7. dxe7 Bxe7 8. e4
{ 8.e3?  d5!  and again Black has the centre. The text move is practically forced, fighting for control of the d5-square. }
8... d6 { Preventing e5. } 9. Bd3 d5 { Break open the center favours Black. }
10. exd5 Nxd5 11. Nxd5 Qxd5 12. O-O c4
{ Continue pushing White's pieces back. } 13. Be2 Qe4
{ Black has a dangerous initiative with actively-placed pieces and space advantage on the queenside. }
