{ White is pinning the d7-pawn so we cannot play d6 to support the c5-pawn. However, the text move allows us a small combination. }
9... O-O { The c5-pawn can be left hanging because it's poisoned. } 10. c4
{ 10.Bxc5  Qa5!  11.Bxe7  Qxa4  and even though White has a rook and two pawns for the bishop pair, Black is better. The bishop pair is an infinite source of power! }
10... d6 { As Black has castled, it's time to defend c5 with the d-pawn. } 11.
Nc3 Nbd7 12. Bc2 Rb8 { Going after the b2-pawn. } 13. Rb1 Ng4
{ The position is similar to the last line, and my conclusion is the same: Black is fine, even though a complex battle lies ahead, where every result is possible. }
