8... e6
{ 9...exd6??  is obviously not possible due to  10.Re1+  and our king is helpless in the centre.   However,  9...O-O!?  is a viable option, intending  10.dxe7  Qxe7  11.Nc3  Bb7  with an unclear position.  With the text move, Black closes the centre and intends to play around the d6-pawn later. True, some kingside dark squares are weakened, but our Dragon bishop is there to take care. If it goes off the board then our position would be treacherous, but I don't see any way for White to achieve this goal any time soon. }
9. Ne5
{ Immediately putting pressure on Black's position. However, this is too straightforward and with some simple moves, Black can kill White's 2-pieces attack. }
