{ This accurate move solves our problem. We intend to exchange some pieces on c6, after which our position will be relieved. }
12. Nc3 Nc6
{ Black is not worse, while White must be careful. The engine shows that the only move to maintain the equality status for White is the strange-looking  13.Bxc6!?  Bxc6  14.f3!?   Note that excessive exchanges on c6 with  13.Nxc6  Bxc6  14.Bxc6  Qxc6  aren't recommended for White, as the d6-pawn is very weak. }
