{ This move is by no means mandatory.  12.exf7  Kd8!  13.Qxf5  Qb6!  is better for Black, although the position still requires precision to win. }
12... Kd8 13. exd7 Qb6
{ The d7-pawn will act as an umbrella for our king. Next, we should activate our pieces with Rf8, a6 and even Nxd7. White has only his queen developed, while most of his forces are sitting on the first rank. Black is winning. }
