{ Our bishop is at the moment more important than the rook as the greedy  11...Bxa1?  is refuted by  12.Qxa1  Rg8  13.d6!  and White is on the verge of winning. The tactical justification of our move is that }
12. Rb1
{ Seemingly White wins material due to the idea of Bxd7+, but as usual, White's hanging pieces allow us to get away. }
12... Qg6 { Both e4 and g2 are hanging. } 13. O-O
{ 13.Qf3  Bg7  gives Black an easy game. } 13... Bd4
