14. Ng3
{ The knight run away to a 'safe' square, but it's time to launch Harry @@StartBracket@@or Huy!@@EndBracket@@ down the board and create havoc! }
14... h5
{ Harry fearlessly marches down the board. It coordinates surprisingly well with Black's pieces and White's king is in real trouble. White needs the engine's help in order to avoid being worse.   I shall just mention that  15.Bd3!  is the best move but after  15...Qg7  our attack is still going strong. }
